org.apache.taverna.workflowmodel

Interface Edit<TargetType>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractActivityEdit, AbstractDataflowEdit, AbstractDataflowInputPortEdit, AbstractDataflowOutputPortEdit, AbstractDatalinkEdit, AbstractDispatchLayerEdit, AbstractMergeEdit, AbstractProcessorEdit, CompoundEdit

    public interface Edit<TargetType>
    The workflow object model exposed by this API is read only. Properties of the model can only be changed through implementations of this interface, this ensures a consistant approach to grouped edits (transactions) and undo / redo support within the UI. It also potentially allows for capture of editing provenance where a workflow is repurposed or created from an aggregate of several others.
    Author:
    Tom Oinn

        Throws:
        EditException - if the edit fails. If an edit throws EditException it should try to ensure the subject is unaltered. Where this is impossible consider breaking edits down into a compound edit.
